The paper focuses on learning video data and discovering complex structures of the video, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method uses a message passing framework and a parameterized kernel, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on two different tasks, video theme classification and video question and answering, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
